es-and-gps-helped-cops-catch-package-thieves\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFAKE AMAZON PACKAGES AND GPS HELPED COPS CATCH PACKAGE THIEVES\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"It was more than a full month before the holiday shopping rush that the U.S.-based seller contacted Amazon. They provided screenshots of their competitor&#x2019;s product being advertised on the &#x201C;Amazon review club&#x201D; Facebook page and even included a link to a negative review that had been written about their product by a man who appears to be deceased."}},{"is":"pull-quote","props":{"text":"“Previously, we had always been able to reinvent our marketing to keep an upper edge. But the fake reviews are intensifying, resulting in significant losses for our business.” ","credit":"Anonymous U.S.-based Amazon seller targeted by a competitor"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"&#x201C;Amazon has not responded to my report that was submitted 2 months ago.&#xA0;Nothing,&#x201D; the seller told Fox. What&#x2019;s more, they say &#x201C;since submitting the report to Amazon in mid-October, [our competitor&#x2019;s] product has gained 100 reviews and our sales continue to plummet.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Fox News was given documentation and evidence of some of these &quot;fake&quot; reviews, but we are unable to reveal the reviews themselves in the interest of protecting the seller whose business has been impacted. Those reviews remain on Amazon as of this writing."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"In the past, Amazon has claimed that less than 1% of reviews on its platform are fake, but with at least 500 million reviews on the site, those fake reviews could still number in the millions by that statistic. One percent of 500 million, a low-ball estimate of the total number of reviews on Amazon, is 5 million reviews, after all."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Amazon is now using &#x201C;machine learning and automated systems&#x201D; to fight the problem of inauthentic reviews, according to a representative who spoke to Fox News. They also pointed out that the company has filed lawsuits against more than 1,000 defendants over the issue."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Amazon was asked about the case of the seller who spoke with Fox News, and who has weathered the holiday shopping season without a response from Amazon, but did not respond in time for the publication of this article."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.foxnews.com\u002Ftech\u002Famazon-execs-grilled-jeered-at-new-york-city-council-hearing-over-hq2\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAMAZON EXECS GRILLED, JEERED AT NEW YORK CITY COUNCIL HEARING OVER HQ2\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"That seller told Fox News that they have not reported the &#x201C;Amazon review club&#x201D; group to Facebook, and suggested they &#x201C;didn&#x2019;t know where to begin.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"A Facebook spokesperson told Fox News that if a user reports a group engaging in this type of activity, the company takes swift action to remove it. Indeed, one of the groups brought to their attention by Fox News was almost immediately taken down."}},{"is":"article-image","props":{"type":"inline","caption":"Fox News passed along this screenshot from a different Amazon review exchange group to Facebook representatives. The company shut the group down almost immediately. (Facebook\u002FFox News)","imageAlt":"Fox News passed along this screenshot from a different Amazon review exchange group to Facebook representatives. The company shut the group down almost immediately. (Facebook\u002FFox News)","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fa57.foxnews.com\u002Fstatic.foxnews.com\u002Ffoxnews.com\u002Fcontent\u002Fuploads\u002F2018\u002F12\u002F640\u002F320\u002FAmazon-review-exchange-SHUT-DOWN.jpg?ve=1&tl=1","copyright":"","source":"","isSpotlight":false,"responsiv